Drivers of Mourning Cloak Population

Packages

library(tidyverse)
library(here)
library(ropls)
library(holodeck)
mocl <- read_rds(here::here("data", "mourning-cloaks", "mocl-seasonal.rds"))

Elizabeth’s note:

I added a response variable of mourning cloak sightings after June 30 because they fly as adults in spring then lay eggs and the 2nd gen flys in fall. Could also play around with timing of these responses - I thought fall adults would work well because summer drought was a weak predictor of total sightings

Fit PCA

pca <- opls(select(mocl, -MOCL, -MOCL_fall, -year))

The variance of the 6 following variables is less than 2.2e-16 in the full or partial (cross-validation) dataset: these variables will be removed:
Apr_cooling_degree_days, Dec_cooling_degree_days, Feb_cooling_degree_days, Jan_cooling_degree_days, Mar_cooling_degree_days, Nov_cooling_degree_days
PCA
20 samples x 78 variables
standard scaling of predictors
6 excluded variables (near zero variance)

get_scores(pca) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = p1, y = p2, color = mocl$MOCL)) +
  geom_point()

get_loadings(pca) %>% 
  arrange(desc(abs(p1)))
